SIMPLE: whack
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Whack
<hw>Whack</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Whacked</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Whacking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. <er>Thwack</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To strike; to beat; to give a heavy or resounding blow
to; to thrash; to make with whacks.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Rodsmen were <qex>whacking</qex>their way through willow
brakes.</q> <rj><qau>G. W. Cable.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To divide into shares; <as>as, to <ex>whack</ex> the
spoils of a robbery</as>; -- often with <ptcl>up</ptcl>.</def>
<mark>[Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whack</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Whack
<hw>Whack</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To strike anything with a smart
blow.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To whack away</b></col>, <cd>to continue striking heavy
blows; <as>as, <ex>to whack away</ex> at a log</as>.</cd>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whack</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Whack
<hw>Whack</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A smart resounding
blow.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A portion; share; allowance.</def>
<mark>[Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>an attempt; <as>as, to take a <ex>whack</ex> at
it.</as></def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs>-- <col><b>Out of whack</b></col>, <cd>out of order.</cd>
<mark>[Slang]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Whacker</ent>⟦br⟧
